main event: Two photographs of gas bubbles apparent in cloudy sky were submitted with the report. No definite identification of the bubbles as being 'unidentified flying objects' could be made from these photographs. Witness stated he observed bright spherical objects moving rapidly in various directions across the sky.
interesting points: The witness observed bright spherical objects moving rapidly in various directions across the sky.
The photographs show a cloudy sky with various dark dots or specks scattered throughout, but no discernible object or structure.
The report includes a classified photograph from the Foreign Technology Division of the AFSC, which appears to depict a celestial object or phenomenon, possibly a nebula or galaxy.
Other similar sightings of bright, spherical objects were reported in the area.
The sighting lasted for approximately 30 seconds before the objects disappeared behind clouds.
photographs: yes, the report includes two photographs of gas bubbles and a classified photograph from the Foreign Technology Division
